Mystical Hero, adept at ranged assaults. Can learn Blizzard, Summon Water Elemental, Brilliance Aura and Mass Teleport.

Attacks land and air units.

Mystical Hero, adept at controlling magic and ranged assaults. Can learn Flame Strike, Banish, Siphon Mana and Phoenix.

Attacks land and air units.

Warrior Hero, adept at offensive combat and disrupting enemy troops. Can learn Storm Bolt, Thunder Clap, Bash and Avatar.

Attacks land units.

Warrior Hero, exceptional at defense and augmenting nearby friendly troops. Can learn Holy Light, Divine Shield, Devotion Aura and Resurrection.

Attacks land units.
A sturdy transport ship capable of carrying units over the sea.

Massive battleship good at destroying enemy ships and bombarding buildings from the sea.

Attacks land units.

A versatile attack ship good at destroying air attackers.

Attacks land and air units.

Swift flying unit, mounted by an Elven warrior. Has the Aerial Shackles ability, which allows it to immobilize and disarm enemy air units temporarily. Can learn Animal War Training, and the Cloud ability.

Attacks land and air units.

Versatile foot soldier. Can learn the Defend ability.

Attacks land units.

Powerful flying creature, mounted by a Dwarven hammer-thrower. Can learn Animal War Training, and the Storm Hammers ability.

Attacks land and air units.

Fast moving flying machine. Excellent at scouting, and effective against air units. Can learn the Flying Machine Bombs and Flak Cannons upgrades.
Can see invisible units.

Attacks air units.

Powerful mounted warrior. Can learn Animal War Training.

Attacks land units.

Supporting spellcaster. Can initially cast Heal, which increases the life of wounded units. Can also learn Dispel Magic and Inner Fire.

Attacks land and air units.

Long-range siege weaponry. Exceptional damage versus buildings, but slow and vulnerable. Can learn the Fragmentation Shards and Flare abilities.

Attacks land units and trees.

Heavily armored vehicle, effective at destroying buildings. Can be upgraded with the Barrage ability.

Attacks buildings.

Basic worker unit. Can harvest gold and lumber, build structures and Repair. Can become Militia.

Attacks land units and trees.
Primary structure, used to train Peasants and receive gathered resources. Can be upgraded to Keep and then Castle to enable the production of additional types of structures and units.
Upgrade to Keep to enable the production of additional types of structures and units.
Upgrade to Castle to enable the production of additional types of structures and units.

Trains Priests, Sorceresses, and Spell Breakers.
Also contains spell upgrades for Priests and Sorceresses, Control Magic, and Magic Sentry.
Provides food, which increases the maximum number of units that can be trained.

Serves as a drop-off point for harvested lumber.
Also contains the upgrades for Lumber Harvesting and Masonry.

Produces Siege Engines, Flying Machines, and Mortar Teams.
Also contains the Flare, Fragmentation Shards, Barrage, Flying Machine Bombs, and Flak Cannons upgrades.

Primary troop production building. Trains Footmen, Riflemen and Knights.
Also contains the Defend, Long Rifles, and Animal War Training upgrades.

Trains Gryphon Riders, and Dragonhawk Riders.
Also contains the Storm Hammers and Cloud upgrades.
Summons Heroes. Revives slain Heroes.
Contains upgrades for improved armor, weaponry and gunpowder.
Basic observation tower. Has no attack, but can be upgraded into a Guard Tower, an Arcane Tower, or a Cannon Tower. Can learn the Magic Sentry ability.

Primary defensive structure. Can learn the Magic Sentry ability.

Attacks land and air units.

Heavy defensive structure. Particularly effective against clusters of troops. Can learn the Magic Sentry ability.

Attacks land units and trees.

Magical defensive tower. Particularly effective against enemy Heroes and spellcasters. Has the Feedback ability, which causes its attacks to destroy mana, dealing extra damage equal to the mana destroyed. Deals bonus damage against summoned units. Can learn the Magic Sentry ability.

Attacks land and air units.
Creates a shop with purchasable items. The items available depend upon what level of upgrade your Town Hall has (Town Hall, Keep, or Castle) and which buildings you have.
Boat construction facility. Produces Human Transport Ships, Human Frigates, and Human Battleships.

Highly skilled sharpshooter, effective against air units. Can gain the Long Rifles upgrade.

Attacks land and air units.

Heavily armored vehicle, effective at destroying buildings. Has the Barrage ability, which fires rockets at nearby enemy air units.

Attacks buildings.

Versatile spellcaster. Can initially cast Slow, which decreases movement and attack speed on enemy units. Can also learn Invisibility and Polymorph.

Attacks land and air units.

Elven warrior trained to destroy spellcasters. Initially has Spell Steal, which manipulates buffs to your advantage, Spell Immunity and Feedback. Can also learn Control Magic.
